Epidemiology, clinical and microbiological characteristics of invasive streptococcal infections in Turkey, 2010-2011. A one-year active surveillance study was conducted to investigate the epidemiological and microbiological characteristics of invasive group A streptococci (GAS) infections in Turkey and to provide data for the establishment of national preventive strategies related to invasive GAS infections. A total of 46 clinical microbiology laboratories from 12 different regions of Turkey (Istanbul Eastern and Western Marmara